The paper proposes a deep learning approach for face detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces new techniques for improving the Faster R-CNN method, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The proposed approach involves multi-scale training and online hard example mining, which are related to multimedia processing and analysis, hence cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also evaluates the proposed approach on two face detection benchmarks, which involves performance evaluation and analysis, hence cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
